1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:09,000
ButterflyLens brings Australia’s rebuilt ALA baseline
into one inspectable evidence workspace.

2
00:00:09,000 --> 00:00:18,000
The catalogue has 463 accepted butterfly species. The public occurrence layer stays withheld
while provider rights remain unresolved—that boundary is intentional.

3
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:26,000
Flickr is the live discovery stream,
not a biodiversity record.

4
00:00:26,000 --> 00:00:34,000
This replay has the deterministic request plan, but no completed immutable result.
Active partial outputs are never substituted into the demo.

5
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:41,000
Governed candidates are designed to flow
through the M5 pipeline.

6
00:00:41,000 --> 00:00:48,000
No authenticated heartbeat, committed batch, or model fingerprint is attached.
YOLOE and BioCLIP remain unfinished, so progress is not invented.

7
00:00:48,000 --> 00:01:00,000
Community expertise enters through blind review. Without enough visible evidence,
I choose “Can’t tell” rather than force an identity.

8
00:01:00,000 --> 00:01:12,000
Only after the draft is locked do source details appear.
This changes local demo state; it submits nothing and verifies no species.

9
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:19,500
The map does not change from one local draft.

10
00:01:19,500 --> 00:01:27,000
A public update needs independent review, rights and sensitivity checks,
and a fingerprinted committed artifact.

11
00:01:27,000 --> 00:01:35,000
Stronger evidence requires repeated, independent reviewers
and an explicit consensus policy.

12
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:43,000
This replay stores no community review or identity.
Unavailable totals stay unavailable; model or majority agreement is not truth.

13
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:51,000
Quality needs a representative audit,
not a convenient sample.

14
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:59,000
Precision and its interval are unavailable—not zero.
The 2,906 valid decodes are diagnostics; zero species are human-verified here.

15
00:01:59,000 --> 00:02:09,500
Bounded model is the bounded live analyst target. It explains deterministic evidence
through read-only tools and never identifies from memory.

16
00:02:09,500 --> 00:02:20,000
For judging, this stored replay preserves the reference-review queue,
exact citations, and tool output. The footer proves no model ran here.

17
00:02:20,000 --> 00:02:25,500
Geographic impact will compare reviewed imagery
with the ALA baseline at safe resolution.

18
00:02:25,500 --> 00:02:31,000
No selectable impact cell is released yet.
Withheld coverage does not mean biological absence.

19
00:02:31,000 --> 00:02:35,500
Export is governed too. ButterflyLens exposes
the release contract, not a pretend download.

20
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:40,000
Unreviewed Flickr candidates can never enter
the final occurrence archive.

21
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:44,000
Codex built and tested the product
and its provenance.

22
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:48,000
It supplied no butterfly identity,
community vote, or scientific ground truth.
